{"id":1906,"date":"2017-09-06T11:55:14","date_gmt":"2017-09-06T10:55:14","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.edlab.org.uk\/?p=1906"},"modified":"2017-09-06T11:55:14","modified_gmt":"2017-09-06T10:55:14","slug":"fighting-for-girls-education","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/fighting-for-girls-education\/","title":{"rendered":"Fighting for Girls Education"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>In Sierra Leone there is a dangerously worrying fact facing vulnerable young girls looking for a fair start in life: they\u2019re simply not being given the opportunity to stay in school. UNICEF research shows that even a single year of secondary education has the potential to increase a girl\u2019s future earnings by up to 25%. Investment in girls\u2019 education also has a multiplier effect: educated girls benefit from better family planning and have healthier children who are more likely to remain in education themselves. But Sierra Leonean girls are increasingly likely to drop out of school at this vital stage.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-1907\" src=\"http:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"663\" height=\"497\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1.png 663w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1-300x225.png 300w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1-120x90.png 120w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1-180x135.png 180w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1-256x192.png 256w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1-360x270.png 360w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled-1-480x360.png 480w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px\" \/><\/p>\n<p><!--more--><\/p>\n<p>Students \u00a0worked to promote public education on the gendered social issue of unequal access to education. To do this they created public events which raised awareness and funds to support the work of the charity <a href=\"https:\/\/www.street-child.co.uk\/\">Street Child<\/a> &#8211; supporting children in the world\u2019s poorest countries.<\/p>\n<p>Visit students\u2019 blog posts on Work with Grimm &amp; Co:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/innovationandeducation.wordpress.com\/2017\/05\/08\/women-rights-questionnaire\/\">Aaishah Aziz<\/a><\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/jasminesawyerblog.wordpress.com\/2017\/03\/08\/fight-for-girls-education-supporting-project\/\">Jasmine Sawyer<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\t\t<style type=\"text\/css\">\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 {\n\t\t\t\tmargin: auto;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 .gallery-item {\n\t\t\t\tfloat: left;\n\t\t\t\tmargin-top: 10px;\n\t\t\t\ttext-align: center;\n\t\t\t\twidth: 33%;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 img {\n\t\t\t\tborder: 2px solid #cfcfcf;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t#gallery-2 .gallery-caption {\n\t\t\t\tmargin-left: 0;\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\/* see gallery_shortcode() in wp-includes\/media.php *\/\n\t\t<\/style>\n\t\t<div id='gallery-2' class='gallery galleryid-1906 gallery-columns-3 gallery-size-medium'><dl class='gallery-item'>\n\t\t\t<dt class='gallery-icon landscape'>\n\t\t\t\t<a href='https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled2.png' title=\"\" data-rl_title=\"\" class=\"rl-gallery-link\" data-rl_caption=\"\" data-rel=\"lightbox-gallery-2\"><img width=\"300\" height=\"225\" src=\"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled2-300x225.png\" class=\"attachment-medium size-medium\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\/64\/2017\/09\/untitled2-300x225.png 300w, https:\/\/mcrblogs.co.uk\/edlab\/wp-content\/uploads\/sites\